Open CTI is a JavaScript API that lets you build and integrate third-party computer-telephony integration (CTI) systems with Salesforce Call Center. To display CTI functionality in Salesforce, Open CTI uses browsers as clients.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

No new features or enhancements are being added to Open CTI. To enable your contact center users to take advantage of the latest phone channel innovations, Salesforce recommends that you modernize your experience by moving to Service Cloud Voice.

The way you implement Open CTI depends on your orgâ€™s user interface. There are separate Open CTI APIs for Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.

IMPORTANT: CTI Toolkit is retired. To continue using CTI functionality, migrate to Salesforce Open CTI.

Typically, CTI vendors or partners create Open CTI implementations. With Open CTI, vendors and partners can:

* Build CTI systems that integrate with Salesforce without the use of CTI adapters.
* Create customizable softphones (call-control tools) that function as fully integrated parts of Salesforce and the Salesforce console.
* Provide users with CTI systems that are browser and platform agnostic.
title: Understanding Salesforce Open CTI
